Why You Stay CompliantThe Trigger Principle: Your account holds a legitimate, assigned GitLab Duo Pro seat. When the automatic setting or your CI script posts the /assign_reviewer @GitLabDuo action, the system executes that request on your behalf as the Maintainer.No Account Sharing: Compliance violations only happen if you share your actual login username, password, or Personal Access Tokens with other human developers so they can pretend to be you.Built-in Intent: GitLab designed the project-wide automatic review setting precisely so that maintainers and project leads can enforce standardized AI quality gates on all code entering their repository.A Quick Warning on GitLab Credits (As of 2026)Keep an eye on how your reviews behave. Under GitLab's updated architecture:GitLab Duo Code Review: This is single-pass. It is covered under your standard Pro/Enterprise seat assignment.Code Review Flow: If your pipeline triggers GitLab's advanced multi-step agentic review, it attributes consumption to the user triggering the flow and draws from GitLab Credits (which are allocated monthly to Premium/Ultimate tiers).
